h_art-the-band.name: Mordecai Mwini Kimeu
h_art-the-band.description: Soulful, African inspired acoustics, smooth, harmonized vocals fused with a touch of well-knit spoken word poetry all blended into one thick pastry of art then served with a witty sense of humor. Slam Africa poetry King. Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/mordecai_dex/

h_art-the-band.name: Wachira Gatama
h_art-the-band.description: Aligning his unwavering dedication to the do-it-yourself work ethic with his undeniable musical versatility, energy and witty nature, he and the band make every performance a pulsating 'fan-magnet'. Slam Africa poetry King. Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/skoko_abednego/

h_art-the-band.name: Kenneth Muya Mukhwana
h_art-the-band.description: Kenneth, together with the band listed among the top 5 artists in terms of radio airplay by the Music Copyright Society of Kenya. Won the Bingwa Award for 'Stage performer of the year 2015' as well as the Mdundo platinum award for having more than 100,000 online downloads. Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/kenchezmuya/

kapenguria-six.name: Kung'u Karumba
kapenguria-six.description: Kung'u Karumba was a Kenyan nationalist and freedom-fighter. He was a member of the Kapenguria Six, along with Bildad Kaggia, Jomo Kenyatta, Fred Kubai, Paul Ngei, and Achieng Oneko.

kapenguria-six.name: Achieng' Oneko
kapenguria-six.description: Ramogi Achieng Oneko was a Kenyan freedom fighter and a politician. In Kenya, he is considered as a national hero. He was born in Tieng'a village in Uyoma sub-location in Bondo District in 1920 and educated at Maseno School.

kapenguria-six.name: Jommo Kenyatta
kapenguria-six.description: Kenyatta was born as Kamau, son of Ngengi, at Ichaweri, southwest of Mount Kenya in the East African highlands. His father was a leader of a small Kikuyu agricultural settlement. About age 10 Kamau became seriously ill with jigger infections in his feet and one leg, and he underwent successful surgery at a newly established Church of Scotland mission.

kapenguria-six.name: Bildad Kaggia
kapenguria-six.description: Bildad Mwaganu Kaggia was a Kenyan nationalist, activist, and politician. Kaggia was a member of the Mau Mau Central Committee. After independence he became a Member of Parliament. He established himself as a militant, fiery nationalist who wanted to serve the poor and landless people

kapenguria-six.name: Fred Kubai
kapenguria-six.description: Fred Kubai was one of the Kapenguria Six, members of the Kenya African Union arrested in 1952, tried and imprisoned. He was a Kikuyu, and a leader of the Kenya Transport Workers Union and the East African Trade Union Congress. Kubai organized attacks against the European government in Nairobi.

kapenguria-six.name: Paul Ngei
kapenguria-six.description: The Honourable Paul Joseph Ngei was a Kenyan politician who was imprisoned for his role in the anti-colonial movement, but who went on to hold several government ministerial positions after Kenya became independent.

sautisol.name: Bien-Aime Baraza
sautisol.description: He is one of the members of Kenya’s top act group Sauti Sol, he is a vocalist, songwriter, guitarist, and pianist. He released a studio album with Aaron Rimbui titled “Bald Men Love Better” in November 2021

sautisol.name: Willis Austin Chimano
sautisol.description: He is Sauti Sol’s baritone vocalist and singer. His vocal range and undoubted skill as an artist have made him a celebrated Kenyan artist.

sautisol.name: Savara Mudigi
sautisol.description: He is the band’s producer, vocalist, and guitarist.

sautisol.name: Polycarp Otieno
sautisol.description: He is the band’s guitarist, producer, songwriter, composer, and singer

Micasa.name: Dr,Duda
Micasa.description: Dr. Duda is responsible for the music production for the band. He was part of a gospel band at his childhood church since the age of 8, played keyboards. He got his nickname from a FL Studio plug-in called Duda. He still uses DAW software, amongst others, including Cubase, Sony Acid, Reason, and Ableton Live.

Micasa.name: J'Something
Micasa.description: J'Something is originally from Portugal. His real name is Joao da Fonseca. He moved to Port Alfred in the Eastern Cape, South Africa when he was seven years old. He was raised by his mother Maria after his parents separated. Joao completed his bachelor's degree in marketing at Stellenbosch University before moving to Johannesburg, where he was a studio manager at the SoulCandi Studios.

Micasa.name: Mo-T
Micasa.description: Mo-T's father, Kgasoane Banza, was part of the South African Afropop band Mango Groove.
